  {"a":"caitlyn_bot","b":"lucian","win":["Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Lucian","Caitlyn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Your 650 auto range plus Headshot lets you poke Lucian every time he steps up to last-hit, and your Q Piltover Peacemaker punishes him when he's stuck behind his caster minions. He has to walk into your range to farm, so trap the lane brush and freeze the wave just outside his reach."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Ace in the Hole gives you a pick threat Lucian lacks, and you still out-range his Piercing Light poke; hold a Yordle Snap Trap on the choke so any dash-in from his E gets rooted and you Headshot for free."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is Lucian's window: with his first item and a Vigilance passive proc off his support, his double-tap Q and Relentless Pursuit reset let him dash on top of you and burst you before you kite out, so respect the all-in when his E is up."},{"when":"Late","text":"Once you hit 2+ items your trap-net-Headshot combo and superior range let you zone him in teamfights; keep a minion or wall between you and stand behind your frontline so his E dash has no safe entry onto you."}],"wants":{"you":["Long freeze just outside his range so he takes Headshots to farm","Traps on the brush and choke to punish his E dash-ins","Peel and a wall behind you so Relentless Pursuit can't reach you"],"foe":["A short wave he can shove and dash onto you with E resets","His support's Vigilance/CC to land his all-in combo","Close-range brawls where his double Q and lifesteal win"]},"early":"You dominate levels 1-2 outright: your 650 range and Headshot out-trade Lucian before he has his E, so poke him every time he approaches a minion and set a trap in the lane brush.","mid":"Through levels 3-6 you keep the range advantage; his Piercing Light needs a minion or you to line up, while your Q and traps make stepping up costly. Zone him off the wave and deny his double-tap trading pattern.","late":"His first-item spike with a Vigilance dash-reset is his one real window, so play safe there; once you complete two items your traps, net kite, and range flip the fight firmly back in your favor.","whys":["Your 650 range and Headshot out-poke Lucian at level 1 before he has any dash.","At level 2 your extra range still punishes every step-up he makes to farm.","By level 3 your Q and trap threat out-trade his short-range double-tap Q.","Through levels 4-5 you keep zoning him off the wave with superior reach.","At level 6 your Ace in the Hole pick threat and range still beat his kit.","With his first item and a Vigilance E-reset, Lucian can dash in and burst you before you kite out.","At 2+ items your trap-net-Headshot combo and range dominate the teamfight again."]},
  {"a":"caitlyn_bot","b":"missfortune","win":["Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You out-range Miss Fortune's 550 auto and her Double Up needs a target to bounce from, so poke her with Headshot autos and Q while she's stuck last-hitting behind minions. Freeze just outside her range and drop a trap on the brush to punish any step-up for her Love Tap reset."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Ace in the Hole is a clean pick tool; Bullet Time is channeled and immobile, so a Yordle Snap Trap or 90 Caliber Net cancels her ult or lets you kite out of the cone entirely while you keep Headshotting her."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With your first item your trap-net-Headshot burst still out-damages her, and you can net away from any Make It Rain slow before her Bullet Time ramps; never stand in the cone and she has no way to force you."},{"when":"Late","text":"In teamfights space so she can never free-fire Bullet Time on you; your range and traps let you sit at max distance, and a well-placed net interrupts her positioning while your team collapses."}],"wants":{"you":["A freeze just outside her 550 range so she eats Headshots to farm","Traps on the brush and choke to deny her Love Tap step-ups","Sidestep or net out of Make It Rain and never stand in Bullet Time"],"foe":["Getting Make It Rain slow onto you to set up Double Up trades","A free channel window for Bullet Time in a chokepoint","A pushed wave so she can Strut and roam or all-in"]},"early":"You win levels 1-2 comfortably: your 650 range beats her 550 auto and her Double Up can't reach you cleanly, so poke every time she creeps up to last-hit and set your brush trap early.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay in your favor; her Make It Rain is her only engage tool and it's easy to sidestep, while your Q and Headshot chip her down every step she takes toward the wave.","late":"You keep the edge into items and teamfights: her Bullet Time is a stationary channel your net and traps shut down, and your superior range means she never gets a safe cone off on you.","whys":["Your 650 range out-pokes Miss Fortune's 550 auto at level 1.","At level 2 she still can't trade back without walking into Headshot range.","By level 3 your Q and trap threat beat her Double Up bounce trades.","Through levels 4-5 you zone her off the wave and deny Love Tap resets.","At level 6 your net and traps cancel her immobile Bullet Time channel.","With first item your trap-net burst out-damages her and you kite Make It Rain.","At 2+ items your range and CC keep her from ever free-firing Bullet Time."]},
  {"a":"caitlyn_bot","b":"nilah","win":["Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Skill","Nilah","Nilah"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Nilah's melee range is your whole early game: at 650 range with Headshot you poke her every time she walks up to farm, and her only gap-closer is her E dash, so trap the brush and freeze the wave just past her reach. Punish hard now because her scaling is brutal once she gets going."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"This is a skill window: her Apotheosis ult gives her big AoE lifesteal and her W lets her dodge your Q, but your Ace in the Hole and net still let you disengage. Don't get greedy into her all-in, but you can still trade if you respect the W damage-reduction window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Nilah spikes hard here: her E dash to a minion or you, plus first-item lifesteal, lets her stick and out-sustain your trades, and her W eats your Q poke. Play for safety, hold your net purely as a disengage, and don't duel her without your support's CC."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late she is a lethal duelist with team-wide healing off her ult, so never let her dash onto you; stand far behind your frontline, drop traps between you and her, and net the instant she E's in. Kite, don't fight her head-on."}],"wants":{"you":["A hard freeze just outside her melee range so she starves for CS","Traps on the brush and choke to punish her E dash-in","Net saved purely to disengage her stick, never to trade"],"foe":["A pushed or short wave she can E-dash across to reach you","Her W up to negate your Q and Headshot poke","First-item lifesteal so she out-sustains extended trades"]},"early":"You crush levels 1-4: Nilah is melee and you out-range her by hundreds of units, so poke her off every last hit, set your brush trap, and try to build a freeze she can't safely walk up to.","mid":"Level 6 is even and skill-dependent; her Apotheosis lifesteal ult and W dodge threaten your all-in, but your net and range still let you escape, so trade on her cooldowns and don't overstay.","late":"Once she hits her first item and beyond she out-sustains and out-sticks you, so stop dueling: play at max range, wall traps between you, and net away the moment she dashes so your team punishes her.","whys":["At level 1 your 650 range dominates melee Nilah before she can reach you.","At level 2 she still can't touch you without burning her E dash.","By level 3 your Q and trap threat punish every step she takes to farm.","Through levels 4-5 you keep zoning her off the wave with pure range.","At level 6 it's a skill window: her ult lifesteal and W dodge offset your Ace pick threat.","With first item her E stick and lifesteal let her out-sustain your trades.","At 2+ items she's a lethal duelist with team healing who beats you head-on if she reaches you."]},
  {"a":"caitlyn_bot","b":"samira","win":["Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Samira","Samira","Samira"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Samira wants to get on top of you, but early she's fragile and short-ranged, so abuse your 650 range and Headshot to poke her every time she steps up. Freeze the wave outside her reach and trap the brush so her W can't safely block your poke; deny her the kill-streak snowball before she has E to dash off minions."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her Inferno Trigger flips this lane: with 5 stacks she ults for massive lifesteal AoE, and her W can windwall your Q and Headshot autos, so never fight into a full Style meter. Save your net as an interrupt, but respect that her all-in with support CC beats yours now."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Samira spikes hard with her first item: her E dash to any minion or champion plus lifesteal lets her stick to you, and her W negates your ranged poke, so play safe and hold net purely to disengage her dash-in."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late she is a top-tier duelist and teamfight threat who resets her ult on kills, so you must never let her reach you; stand behind your frontline, drop traps between you, and net the instant she E's in so your team bursts her before Inferno Trigger heals her up."}],"wants":{"you":["A freeze just outside her range so she starves and can't proc W value","Traps on the brush and choke to punish her E dash-in","Net saved to disengage her dash, never wasted into her W window"],"foe":["A short wave and minions to E-dash off to reach you","5 Style stacks up so she can Inferno Trigger your all-in","Her W ready to block your Q and Headshot poke"]},"early":"You own levels 1-4: Samira is a short-range brawler and you out-range her hugely, so poke her every step, set your brush trap, and freeze so she can't stack Style safely.","mid":"Level 6 flips to her: Inferno Trigger's lifesteal plus her windwall W turn your poke into her fuel, so stop dueling once her meter is full and save your net as an interrupt.","late":"Through her first item and beyond she out-sticks and out-sustains you with E dashes and ult resets, so play at max range, wall traps between you, and net away the instant she engages.","whys":["At level 1 your 650 range dominates short-range Samira before she can engage.","At level 2 she still can't reach you without burning tempo, so you keep poking.","By level 3 your Q and trap threat punish every step she takes to stack Style.","Through levels 4-5 you keep her starved and off the wave with pure range.","At level 6 Inferno Trigger's lifesteal and her windwall W flip the all-in to her.","With first item her E stick and lifesteal let her out-sustain and beat your trades.","At 2+ items she's a lethal resetting duelist who wins the moment she reaches you."]},
  {"a":"caitlyn_bot","b":"senna","win":["Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Senna"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Early you out-range and out-tempo Senna hard: she's a slow-attacking soul collector, so punish her with Headshot autos and Q every time she steps up to last-hit or grab a soul. Trap the brush, freeze just past her range, and deny her souls to slow her scaling before it becomes a problem."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Ace in the Hole out-picks her global Dawning Shadow, and you still win the short-range fight; her Q Piercing Darkness needs a target to heal or poke, so zone her off souls and keep Headshotting while she's stuck farming stacks."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With your first item your trap-net-Headshot burst still out-damages a Senna who's building up; keep denying souls and abuse her low base attack speed and range so she never stabilizes her stacking curve."},{"when":"Late","text":"This is Senna's window: with 2+ items and a pile of souls she out-ranges even you, scales infinitely, and provides team-wide utility with her E camouflage and W root, so play safe, respect her range, and let your team engage while you clean up from max distance."}],"wants":{"you":["A freeze just outside her range so she can't farm CS or souls safely","Traps and poke to deny her soul stacks and slow her scaling","Early all-ins with support CC before she out-ranges you"],"foe":["Free souls and passive farm to stack range and damage","Late-game range where she out-zones even Caitlyn","Her W root and E stealth to set up picks in teamfights"]},"early":"You dominate levels 1-2: Senna's low base attack speed and range let you poke her freely with Headshot every time she steps up, so trap the brush and deny her early souls.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay yours; your Ace out-picks her global ult and your poke zones her off souls, so keep her starved and punish every last-hit she reaches for.","late":"The lane flips once she stacks: at 2+ items and many souls Senna out-ranges and out-scales you with huge utility, so stop trading, play at max distance, and let your frontline engage while you clean up.","whys":["At level 1 your range and Headshot dominate slow-attacking Senna.","At level 2 you keep poking her every step she takes toward CS or souls.","By level 3 your Q and trap threat punish her weak early trading.","Through levels 4-5 you zone her off souls and stall her scaling.","At level 6 your Ace out-picks her global ult and you win the short fight.","With first item your burst still beats an under-stacked Senna.","At 2+ items her stacked souls out-range and out-scale even you, flipping the matchup."]},
  {"a":"caitlyn_bot","b":"seraphine","win":["Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Against an APC Seraphine you out-range and out-DPS her: she leans on her Q poke and E slow-into-root combo, so play behind your minions to dodge her skillshots and Headshot her every time she steps up to poke. Trap the choke so any E she throws is answered by your net-trap punish."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her Encore is a strong AoE charm, but it needs to hit a target to chain to you and it's telegraphed; your Ace in the Hole and net let you disengage or pick her, and you still win the raw lane trade if you stay behind minions and out-poke her Q."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With your first item your trap-net-Headshot burst deletes a squishy Seraphine, and she has no dash to escape it; hold your net for her E engage and blow her up whenever she steps into your range without her charm ready."},{"when":"Late","text":"In teamfights her Encore can catch your whole team, so spread out and never clump; but as a duelist she's immobile and squishy, so your range and traps let you sit at max distance and delete her the moment she's caught out."}],"wants":{"you":["Standing behind minions to body-block her Q and E skillshots","Traps on the choke to punish her E slow-root engage","Net held to disengage or pick her since she has no dash"],"foe":["Landing E slow into a root to set up her Q and Encore","A clumped team so Encore charms multiple targets","Poke range to whittle you before you can close a trade"]},"early":"You win levels 1-2: sit behind your minions to dodge her Q and E, and punish every step-up with Headshot since she's an immobile short-poke mage with no early kill pressure on you.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay in your favor; her Encore charm is telegraphed and needs a target to chain, so respect the cooldown but keep out-poking her and zoning her off the wave with your range.","late":"You hold the edge into items: your trap-net burst deletes a dashless Seraphine, so just avoid clumping into her Encore in fights, spread out, and pick her from max range whenever she's exposed.","whys":["At level 1 your range and Headshot out-poke immobile Seraphine.","At level 2 you keep punishing her step-ups from behind your minions.","By level 3 your Q and trap threat beat her short-range poke trades.","Through levels 4-5 you zone her off the wave with superior range.","At level 6 your Ace and net beat her telegraphed Encore in the 2v2.","With first item your trap-net burst deletes the dashless, squishy Seraphine.","At 2+ items your range and CC let you pick her off before her charm lands."]},
  {"a":"caitlyn_bot","b":"sivir","win":["Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Sivir"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"With Headshot up and a Yordle Snap Trap planted in the lane bush, you out-range Sivir's Boomerang Blade (Q) by a mile; auto her whenever she steps up to last-hit and she can't retaliate without eating a full trade. She has to Spellshield (E) reactively, so bait it with a raw auto, then land your empowered Headshot or a 90 Caliber Net (E) reposition once her shield is on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Ace in the Hole (R) lets you finish a Sivir who tried to Ricochet-shove and back off; snipe her from screen-away as she walks to base or under her own tower after a trade. She has no combat ult to answer it, so any HP she leaves the lane on is deletable if your support pins her."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You spike hard the moment you complete your first item; your range plus trap-into-Headshot burst still beats Sivir's DPS in a straight 2v2 before her On the Hunt (R) becomes a fight-swinging engage tool. Trade on her Q/E cooldowns and keep last-hitting behind minions so Boomerang Blade only clips one target."},{"when":"Late","text":"This is where Sivir flips ahead: On the Hunt (R) gives her whole team movement speed to close your range gap and her Spellshield eats your Ace in the Hole or engage CC. In 5v5 you must position on the flank, kite with your superior range, and never get caught in the Ricochet bounce range while her team is speeding at you."}],"wants":{"you":["Long-range pokes with Headshot autos and Piltover Peacemaker before she can shield","Traps in chokepoints so she can't dodge or reposition freely","Ending the lane phase with a lead before her R scales the teamfight"],"foe":["A well-timed Spellshield to negate your net, ult, or a key poke","Reaching 2+ items and On the Hunt to close range and start fights","Grouped 5v5s where her team speed nullifies your kiting"]},"early":"You own levels 1-2 outright: your auto range and Headshot mean every time Sivir walks up for a CS you can punish, and she has no way to trade back without a Boomerang Blade she has to aim through minions. Plant a trap in the bush and zone her off the wave.","mid":"Through levels 3-6 you keep the range advantage; poke with Piltover Peacemaker and empowered autos, force her to burn Spellshield defensively, then commit once it's down. Ace in the Hole at 6 punishes any low-HP retreat she makes across the lane.","late":"Once Sivir has 2+ items and On the Hunt online, the matchup inverts: her Spellshield eats your key ability and her team speed erases your range edge, so play the flank, respect the engage, and win with positioning rather than a lane duel.","whys":["Level 1 favours you because your auto range and Headshot out-trade Sivir before her Q comes online.","Level 2 stays yours as your longer range punishes her every time she steps up to last-hit.","Level 3 is yours since traps plus poke force her to shield defensively instead of trading.","Levels 4-5 you keep the lead by trading on her Q and E cooldowns from behind minions.","Level 6 favours you because Ace in the Hole snipes any low Sivir who tries to shove and retreat.","First item is still yours as your range and burst beat her DPS before On the Hunt matters.","At 2+ items Sivir flips ahead because Spellshield and her team-wide speed close your range gap in fights."]},
  {"a":"caitlyn_bot","b":"smolder","win":["Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Smolder is one of the weakest early laners in the game because his Super Scorcher Breath (Q) needs stacks to hurt; you punish that window ruthlessly with Headshot autos and a Yordle Snap Trap under his feet. Every time he walks up to farm his passive stacks you get a free empowered auto, and he can't trade back with a low-stack Q. Zone him off CS to starve the very stacks he needs to come online."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Ace in the Hole (R) lets you punish a Smolder who's forced to over-extend for stacks or turns to run; snipe him as he retreats before Mobile Explosive Debris (R) gives him waveclear and safety. He has no dash to dodge it once your support lands CC. The more you deny him now the later his stacked Q spike arrives."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first item keeps you ahead: your range and Headshot burst still out-duel a Smolder who hasn't hit his 225-stack threshold, so keep trading on his Q cooldown and freezing him off farm. His E (Flap, Flap, Flap) gives him mobility and a shield, so bait it before you commit your net."},{"when":"Late","text":"Smolder flips the matchup once fully stacked: his Q becomes a low-cooldown execute-tier nuke that out-ranges even you and his R clears waves from safety. In 5v5 you must burst him or peel him before that stacked Q chunks your team; play the flank, use your range to threaten but respect that a stacked Smolder now out-damages you."}],"wants":{"you":["Punishing his stack-starved early with trap-into-Headshot trades","Freezing the wave to deny his passive stacks and delay his spike","Snowballing a lead before his Q reaches full stacks"],"foe":["Farming safely to hit 225 stacks and unlock his execute Q","Using E's mobility and shield to survive to the late game","Grouped fights where his stacked Q out-ranges and out-damages you"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are firmly yours: Smolder is helpless before his stacks, so use your superior range and Headshot to punish every last-hit he goes for. Plant a trap in his path and let your support poke; the goal is to starve his stacks so his power spike arrives late.","mid":"Through 3-6 you keep dominating; he can't trade back with a weak Q, and Ace in the Hole at 6 punishes any greedy extension for stacks. Freeze the wave, deny CS, and force him to farm under tower where he stacks slower.","late":"A fully-stacked Smolder inverts everything: his Q becomes a long-range execute that out-damages you and his R clears from safety, so shift to flank positioning, burst or peel him fast, and stop treating it as a lane duel you win.","whys":["Level 1 is yours because Smolder is stack-starved and can't answer your ranged Headshot trades.","Level 2 favours you as your range punishes every last-hit while his Q is still weak.","Level 3 stays yours since traps and freezes deny the stacks he desperately needs.","Levels 4-5 you keep the lead trading on his Q cooldown and starving his farm.","Level 6 is yours because Ace in the Hole punishes any over-extension for stacks.","First item is still yours as your burst out-duels an unstacked Smolder.","At 2+ items Smolder flips ahead once his stacked Q becomes a long-range execute that out-damages you."]},
  {"a":"caitlyn_bot","b":"swain","win":["Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Swain","Caitlyn","Caitlyn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Against a bot-lane Swain your whole plan is to never get hit by Nevermove (W) or Death's Hand (Q); stay behind your caster minions and poke with Headshot autos from max range. His only kill pressure comes from landing the W root, so respect that zone and drop a Yordle Snap Trap on the spot he wants to root you from. Trade when his Q is down and his soul fragments are low."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"This is Swain's window: Demonic Ascension (R) turns him into a sustain-tank that heals off everyone nearby, and if his support lands CC he can walk you down through your kite. Do not fight him inside his ult radius; back off, let it expire, then re-engage. Ace in the Hole (R) can chunk him from range but won't out-race his drain healing in a straight brawl."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once you complete your first item you reclaim the edge: your range lets you poke Swain down before he ever lands a root, and he's squishy the moment his R isn't up. Keep spacing so Nevermove can't catch you, use your net to disengage his all-in, and farm the lane from safety."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late you out-range and out-DPS Swain hard in 5v5 as long as you never get pulled by Nevermove; his R healing means nothing if you kite outside his radius. Position on the flank, let your frontline soak his W, and shred him with your range once his one engage tool is spent."}],"wants":{"you":["Poking with max-range Headshot autos from behind minions","Dodging Nevermove and punishing its long cooldown","Kiting outside his R radius so his drain healing is wasted"],"foe":["Landing Nevermove root to lock you for a Q-E-R combo","Fighting inside Demonic Ascension where he heals off your team","Support CC that pins you so he can walk you down at 6"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are yours: Swain has no way to threaten you at range, so poke him with Headshot every time he steps up and stay behind minions so Nevermove can't land. Plant a trap on his likely root spot and starve his soul fragments.","mid":"Through 3-5 you keep control with pure spacing, but level 6 flips to Swain: Demonic Ascension makes him a healing bruiser who wins any fight inside his radius, especially with support CC. Disengage, wait it out, then resume poking once it drops.","late":"With items you pull back ahead decisively; you out-range and out-DPS Swain as long as you never eat Nevermove, so kite outside his R radius, let your frontline absorb his root, and delete him from max range in teamfights.","whys":["Level 1 is yours because Swain can't answer your ranged pokes and has no engage yet.","Level 2 favours you as Headshot punishes every step-up while you stay out of W range.","Level 3 stays yours since dodging Nevermove leaves him with no kill pressure.","Levels 4-5 you keep poking safely and punishing his long root cooldown.","Level 6 flips to Swain because Demonic Ascension turns him into a healing bruiser who wins fights in his radius.","First item swings back to you as your range pokes him down before he can root.","At 2+ items you out-range and out-DPS him as long as you kite outside his ult and dodge Nevermove."]},
  {"a":"caitlyn_bot","b":"tristana","win":["Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Tristana"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Early you out-range Tristana by a wide margin since her level-1 attack range is short; punish every last-hit with Headshot autos and drop a Yordle Snap Trap where she'd want to Rocket Jump (W) in. Her only gap-closer is that jump, so if she uses W aggressively, net (E) away and she's stranded with no escape for a full trade. Keep the wave in the middle so she can't farm without stepping into your poke range."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Ace in the Hole (R) punishes a Trist who Rocket Jumps in and gets caught out; if she W's onto you and your support lands CC, she has no second dash to leave. Meanwhile Buster Shot (R) is her disengage/knockback, so bait it before you commit your net. Any low-HP retreat she makes is snipeable from across the lane."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first item keeps you ahead; your range still lets you whittle her down before she reaches the hyper-scaling range she gets from her passive per level. Trade on her W cooldown, freeze her off farm, and remember Explosive Charge (E) stacks on her target, so break the trade before it detonates for big damage."},{"when":"Late","text":"Tristana flips the matchup late: her per-level range growth catches up to yours, Rocket Jump resets on kills for repeated all-ins, and Explosive Charge plus her attack speed shred you in extended fights. In 5v5 respect her jump-reset threat, peel with your net, and don't let her dive your backline off a low-HP pick."}],"wants":{"you":["Punishing her short early range with Headshot poke","Trapping her Rocket Jump landing spots to strand her","Snowballing a lead before her per-level range scales up"],"foe":["Reaching late game where her range growth matches yours","Rocket Jump resets to chain all-ins and dives","Explosive Charge detonations plus attack speed in extended fights"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 heavily favour you: Tristana's early range is short, so you punish every last-hit with Headshot while she can't trade back. Plant a trap on her likely Rocket Jump spot and hold the wave central so she farms inside your poke.","mid":"Through 3-6 you keep the range lead; force her to burn Rocket Jump defensively, then punish the cooldown, and use Ace in the Hole at 6 to snipe any low retreat. Break trades before Explosive Charge detonates.","late":"Tristana inverts the lane late once her per-level range catches yours and Rocket Jump reset lets her chain all-ins; her E and attack speed melt you in extended fights, so peel with your net, respect the dive threat, and never feed her a reset off a pick.","whys":["Level 1 is yours because Tristana's short early range can't answer your Headshot poke.","Level 2 favours you as every step-up to last-hit eats an empowered auto.","Level 3 stays yours since traps punish her only gap-closer, Rocket Jump.","Levels 4-5 you keep the lead trading on her W cooldown and freezing her off farm.","Level 6 is yours because Ace in the Hole snipes any low Trist who jumped in and got caught.","First item is still yours as your range whittles her down before her per-level scaling arrives.","At 2+ items Tristana flips ahead once her range growth, jump resets, and E detonations overpower you."]},
  {"a":"caitlyn_bot","b":"twitch","win":["Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You dominate a lane Twitch because his early damage is all poison-stack DPS with no burst, and his short auto range means you Headshot him freely every time he creeps up. His real threat is Ambush (Q) stealth ganks, so ward the flanks and drop a Yordle Snap Trap on the bush he'd re-stealth from. If he Ambushes in, net (E) away and punish him hard once he's revealed with no escape."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Ace in the Hole (R) plus your range keep you ahead at 6; Twitch's Spray and Pray (R) is a teamfight tool, not a duel button, so in a 2v2 you out-poke and out-range him before he ever gets to line you up. Snipe him if he's forced to reveal and retreat. Keep vision so his stealth roams don't catch you off guard."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first-item spike holds the lead; you out-range and out-trade Twitch, who has no reliable way to close on you without burning Ambush. Freeze the wave off him, deny his Deadly Venom stacks from ramping, and keep last-hitting from max range so his contaminate never chunks you."},{"when":"Late","text":"You stay ahead even late if you position correctly: Twitch's Spray and Pray plus Contaminate can shred a grouped team, but you out-range him, so kite on the flank and never let him get stealth-range on your backline. Keep pink wards down, respect the Ambush timing, and shred him first with your superior range before his ramping DPS gets going."}],"wants":{"you":["Punishing his short range with constant Headshot poke","Warding flanks and trapping his stealth re-entry spots","Keeping the lane at max range so his poison never ramps on you"],"foe":["Ambush stealth ganks to catch you out of position","Ramping Deadly Venom stacks plus Contaminate burst","Spray and Pray piercing a grouped team in late 5v5s"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are firmly yours: Twitch has no early burst and short range, so you Headshot him at will while he can only stack weak poison. Ward the flank bushes, plant a trap on his stealth path, and zone him off CS.","mid":"Through 3-6 you keep control; his R is a fight tool not a duel answer, so you out-poke him in the 2v2 and Ace in the Hole punishes any forced retreat. Deny his venom stacks and keep vision so Ambush can't surprise you.","late":"You hold the edge into the late game as long as you position on the flank and keep pinks down; Twitch's ramping DPS and Spray and Pray are lethal to a grouped team, but your range lets you kite and shred him before he lines you up.","whys":["Level 1 is yours because Twitch has no early burst and can't answer your Headshot poke.","Level 2 favours you as your range punishes every last-hit while his poison is weak.","Level 3 stays yours since warding and traps neutralize his Ambush ganks.","Levels 4-5 you keep the lead freezing him off farm and denying venom stacks.","Level 6 is yours because your poke and Ace in the Hole beat his teamfight-only ult in a duel.","First item is still yours as you out-range and out-trade a Twitch with no gap-closer.","At 2+ items you stay ahead by kiting on the flank and shredding him before his ramping DPS starts."]},
  {"a":"caitlyn_bot","b":"varus","win":["Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Varus","Caitlyn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You out-range Varus and punish his poke pattern: he wants to charge Piercing Arrow (Q) to bully you, but a charging Varus is slowed and telegraphed, so step behind minions and Headshot him back before he releases. Drop a Yordle Snap Trap on the spot he stands to charge Q and force him to give up the poke. Trade on his Q cooldown, and note his Blighted Quiver (W) stacks only ramp if he lands autos, so deny him those."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Ace in the Hole (R) punishes a Varus who over-pokes and drops low; you out-range his R, Chain of Corruption, which is an engage/AoE-root ult, not a snipe. Bait his R before committing since it's his only lockdown, then all-in once it's down. Keep spacing so the root doesn't chain from a minion or your support onto you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is Varus's window: on-hit or lethality Varus spikes hard on his first item, his W stacks detonate for big chunks, and his poke-plus-root can win a 2v2 if your support gets caught. Respect his damage here, don't greed trades into a stacked W, and use your net to disengage his all-in rather than duel him head-on."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late you reclaim the edge with your range and utility; Varus's Chain of Corruption is a one-shot engage that, once dodged or baited, leaves him a squishy immobile carry you out-range. Position on the flank, make him blow R on your frontline, then kite and shred him from max range before his W stacks can detonate on you."}],"wants":{"you":["Punishing his telegraphed Q charge with Headshot poke from behind minions","Trapping his charge spot to deny the poke pattern","Baiting Chain of Corruption then all-in on the cooldown"],"foe":["First-item spike where W stacks detonate for big damage","Landing Chain of Corruption to root and all-in your carry","Poke-plus-root pressure that catches an out-of-position support"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are yours: a charging Piercing Arrow slows and telegraphs Varus, so you step behind minions and Headshot him before he releases. Plant a trap on his charge spot and deny his W auto-stacks so his poke never ramps.","mid":"You hold through 4-5, but Varus spikes on his first item at level 5-6: his W detonations and poke-plus-root can flip a 2v2 if your support is caught, so respect his damage and disengage with net rather than dueling. At 6, Ace in the Hole and your range still let you punish an over-extended Varus.","late":"Late you pull back ahead; once Chain of Corruption is dodged or baited onto your frontline, Varus is an immobile squishy you out-range, so flank, make him waste R, then kite and shred him before his W stacks detonate.","whys":["Level 1 is yours because a telegraphed, slowed Q charge lets you Headshot Varus first.","Level 2 favours you as you poke from behind minions and deny his W auto-stacks.","Level 3 stays yours since trapping his charge spot shuts down his poke pattern.","Levels 4-5 you keep the lead trading on his Q cooldown before his item spike lands.","Level 6 is yours because Ace in the Hole and your range punish an over-poked Varus.","First item flips to Varus because his W detonations and poke-plus-root can win the 2v2.","At 2+ items you reclaim the edge by baiting Chain of Corruption then out-ranging an immobile Varus."]},
  {"a":"caitlyn_bot","b":"vayne","win":["Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Level 1-3","text":"Caitlyn's huge range gap over short-range Vayne lets her poke for free and deny CS."},{"when":"Trap + net all-in","text":"Snap Trap Headshot with support CC bursts the fragile early Vayne before she Condemns away."},{"when":"Full build","text":"This bespoke matchup keeps Caitlyn ahead all game: she must close it out in lane before Vayne's true-damage scaling matters."}],"wants":{"you":["Abuse the range gap every wave","Trap her Q tumble paths","Snowball a big lane lead","End before she out-scales"],"foe":["Survive to two-three items","Silver Bolts true damage","Condemn stun on the wall","Reach hypercarry late game"]},"early":"Caitlyn hard-bullies Vayne in the first three levels: one of the largest range gaps in the game means she pokes with Headshot and autos while Vayne, with her tiny range, cannot retaliate without eating damage. Vayne is fragile and item-dependent early, so Caitlyn should zone her off CS with traps and threaten kills constantly. This is a lane Caitlyn is meant to dominate.","mid":"First-item Caitlyn keeps sieging and zoning Vayne, who is still ramping toward her item spikes. Level 6 Ace in the Hole punishes a low Vayne, though her Condemn and Tumble make her slippery. Caitlyn's whole plan is to convert her early range dominance into a big gold and plate lead so Vayne never gets to scale into her hypercarry late game.","late":"Vayne is a premier late-game hypercarry whose Silver Bolts true damage normally overtakes Caitlyn, but in this bespoke read Caitlyn holds the edge by closing the game before that happens. Late, she must kite at absolute max range, use net to break Vayne's engage, and never let Vayne get on top of her in the fog. A snowballed lane lead is what keeps Caitlyn ahead all the way through.","whys":["Caitlyn's massive range gap over short-range Vayne wins the level 1 trade outright.","Levels 2-3 Headshot poke lets Caitlyn zone a fragile Vayne off CS.","Trap plus net plus support CC bursts Vayne before her Condemn escape.","First-item Caitlyn sieges and denies Vayne's scaling with a plate lead.","Ace in the Hole picks a low Vayne who is still item-dependent at six.","Caitlyn's range keeps snowballing the lead through the mid-late transition.","Here Caitlyn closes the game before Vayne's true-damage hypercarry scaling flips it."]},
  {"a":"caitlyn_bot","b":"veigar","win":["Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Level 1-3","text":"Caitlyn out-ranges the melee-range-caster Veigar and pokes him off farm before he stacks AP."},{"when":"Trap + net all-in","text":"Snap Trap Headshot with support CC bursts the squishy, immobile Veigar before he lands Event Horizon."},{"when":"Full build","text":"Veigar is a burst mage, not a scaling ADC; Caitlyn's range and pick threat keep her ahead if she respects his stun."}],"wants":{"you":["Out-range his Baleful Strike poke","Trap and net through his cage","Dodge Event Horizon edges","Punish his immobility"],"foe":["Stack AP with Baleful Strike","Land Event Horizon stun","Combo Q+W burst","One-shot you with R"]},"early":"As a bot-lane mage Veigar out-ranges some ADCs, but Caitlyn's game-leading auto range plus Headshot lets her poke him whenever he steps up to farm-stack with Baleful Strike. He is squishy and completely immobile, so Caitlyn threatens constant trades and traps. She should punish every Q he uses on minions by stepping up for a Headshot exchange.","mid":"First-item Caitlyn keeps zoning Veigar, who relies on landing Event Horizon to do anything. Level 6 Ace in the Hole gives her a pick on a low, stationary Veigar. The danger is his stun-combo burst, so Caitlyn must position to dodge the cage edges and never walk into a point-blank W; if she respects the stun, her range dominates the lane.","late":"Veigar is a burst caster, not a scaling marksman, so he does not out-DPS Caitlyn in sustained fights the way a hypercarry ADC would. Late game the threat is a single Event Horizon stun into R deleting Caitlyn, so she plays at max range, holds net to break line-of-sight or reposition, and picks him with Ace in the Hole. Respecting his one combo keeps her ahead at full build.","whys":["Caitlyn's leading auto range pokes Veigar off his level 1 farm-stacking.","Levels 2-3 Headshot punishes Veigar every time he Qs a minion.","Trap plus net plus support CC bursts the immobile Veigar before his cage lands.","First-item Caitlyn zones Veigar, who can only act by landing Event Horizon.","Ace in the Hole picks a low, stationary Veigar at level six.","Caitlyn's range keeps her safe as long as she dodges the cage edges.","Veigar is a burst mage, not a scaling ADC, so Caitlyn's range holds at full build."]},
  {"a":"caitlyn_bot","b":"xayah","win":["Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Xayah"],"spikes":[{"when":"Level 1-3","text":"Caitlyn out-ranges Xayah's shorter autos and pokes with Headshot before Xayah stacks feathers."},{"when":"Trap + net all-in","text":"Snap Trap Headshot with support CC can burst Xayah before she uses Featherstorm invulnerability."},{"when":"Full build","text":"Xayah's feather-recall AoE and crit scaling out-DPS Caitlyn in extended teamfights, and R gives her a defensive reset."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke before she stacks feathers","Trap her Bladecaller angles","Trade when R is down","Siege turrets with range lead"],"foe":["Stack feathers for Bladecaller roots","Reach crit item spikes","Featherstorm to dodge your R","Scale AoE DPS late"]},"early":"Caitlyn out-ranges Xayah in the first three levels, poking with Headshot while Xayah has shorter auto range and needs to stack feathers before her Bladecaller root is threatening. Caitlyn should trade early and deny CS before Xayah gets rolling. Watch for feathers on the ground, since a full Bladecaller root plus support engage is Xayah's main early counterplay.","mid":"First-item Caitlyn keeps the range and siege lead, using traps to zone Xayah off the wave. Level 6 gives Caitlyn Ace in the Hole, but Xayah's Featherstorm can dodge it with invulnerability, so timing matters. Caitlyn should press her early advantage into plates before Xayah's crit and feather-stacking scale up.","late":"By full build Xayah out-scales Caitlyn: her Bladecaller feather recall does big AoE damage in teamfights, Featherstorm gives untargetable safety plus a root setup, and her crit DPS overtakes Caitlyn's utility damage. Caitlyn must kite at max range, save net for Xayah's engage, and pick with Ace in the Hole when Featherstorm is down. In extended fights a fed Xayah simply carries harder.","whys":["Caitlyn's base range beats Xayah's shorter autos in the level 1 trade.","Levels 2-3 Headshot poke punishes Xayah before she stacks feathers.","Trap plus net plus support CC can burst Xayah before Featherstorm invulnerability.","First-item Caitlyn sieges and zones Xayah off the wave for plates.","Ace in the Hole threatens Xayah when Featherstorm is on cooldown.","Caitlyn's range keeps her ahead through the mid-late transition.","At full build Xayah's feather AoE, crit, and R safety out-scale Caitlyn."]},
  {"a":"caitlyn_bot","b":"zeri","win":["Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Level 1-3","text":"Caitlyn out-ranges Zeri's short Q auto-range and pokes her hard before Zeri gets items and move-speed rolling."},{"when":"Trap + net all-in","text":"Snap Trap Headshot with support CC bursts the squishy Zeri before her E dash and R shield ramp."},{"when":"Full build","text":"This bespoke read keeps Caitlyn ahead by winning lane and denying Zeri the items her hyper-mobile late game needs."}],"wants":{"you":["Abuse the early range gap","Trap her E dash paths","Deny items before she snowballs","Punish her weak early laning"],"foe":["Farm safely to items","Ramp move speed with R","Kite with Q and E","Reach hyper-mobile late game"]},"early":"Caitlyn dominates the first three levels: Zeri's Q functions as a short-range auto, so Caitlyn heavily out-ranges her and pokes with Headshot while Zeri has weak early laning and no way to trade back. Zeri is very item-dependent, so Caitlyn should zone her off CS with traps and threaten kills constantly. This is one of Zeri's worst early lanes.","mid":"First-item Caitlyn keeps zoning Zeri, who is still ramping toward her item spikes and move-speed engine. Level 6 Ace in the Hole punishes a low Zeri, though her E dash and R shield make her slippery. Caitlyn's plan is to convert her early range beatdown into a big lead so Zeri never reaches the fed, hyper-mobile state where she takes over.","late":"Zeri is a scaling, mobility-driven carry who can spiral out of control if she gets items, but in this bespoke read Caitlyn stays ahead by suffocating her farm early. Late, Caitlyn kites at max range, uses traps and net to punish Zeri's dash paths, and picks with Ace in the Hole. Keeping Zeri item-starved is what preserves Caitlyn's edge all the way to full build.","whys":["Caitlyn heavily out-ranges Zeri's short Q-auto in the level 1 trade.","Levels 2-3 Headshot poke punishes Zeri's weak, item-dependent early laning.","Trap plus net plus support CC bursts the squishy Zeri before her E and R ramp.","First-item Caitlyn zones and denies Zeri the items she needs to scale.","Ace in the Hole picks a low Zeri who has not yet spiked at six.","Caitlyn keeps snowballing the lead as Zeri struggles to farm safely.","Here Caitlyn stays item-ahead and denies Zeri's hyper-mobile late-game takeover."]},
  {"a":"caitlyn_bot","b":"ziggs","win":["Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn","Caitlyn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Level 1-2","text":"Caitlyn can step up and auto-poke Ziggs with Headshot before he zones with Bouncing Bomb."},{"when":"Trap + net all-in","text":"Snap Trap Headshot with support CC bursts the squishy, immobile Ziggs before he Satchels away."},{"when":"Full build","text":"Ziggs is a poke mage, not a scaling ADC; Caitlyn's range and pick threat keep her ahead if she dodges his Q."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Bouncing Bomb, close for autos","Trap his Satchel landing spots","All-in his immobility","Siege with your own range"],"foe":["Zone the wave with Q","Poke you off with W and E","Satchel Charge to escape","Minefield to deny all-ins"]},"early":"Ziggs is a poke mage who wants to zone with Bouncing Bomb, but Caitlyn's leading auto range and Headshot let her step up and punish him between Q cooldowns. He is squishy and only has Satchel Charge for mobility, so Caitlyn threatens trap-net all-ins whenever he uses Q on the wave. She should weave in autos rather than sit passively eating poke.","mid":"First-item Caitlyn keeps pressuring Ziggs, and level 6 Ace in the Hole gives her a pick on a low, stationary Ziggs. His Minefield and Satchel provide some self-peel, so Caitlyn should force fights when Satchel is down and collapse with her support. Converting early pressure into plates keeps her tempo ahead of his poke.","late":"Ziggs is a poke and waveclear mage, not a scaling marksman, so he does not out-DPS Caitlyn in sustained teamfights the way a hypercarry ADC would. Late game his threat is long-range Q/R chip and Minefield zoning, so Caitlyn plays at max range, respects Satchel disengage, and picks him with Ace in the Hole. Because he offers no scaling carry damage, Caitlyn's range edge holds through full build.","whys":["Caitlyn steps up and Headshot-pokes Ziggs between Bouncing Bomb cooldowns at level 1.","Levels 2-3 Caitlyn punishes Ziggs whenever he uses Q on the wave.","Trap plus net plus support CC bursts the immobile Ziggs before he Satchels out.","First-item Caitlyn pressures and zones a squishy Ziggs off the wave.","Ace in the Hole picks a low, stationary Ziggs at level six.","Caitlyn's range keeps her ahead as long as she dodges his poke.","Ziggs is a poke mage, not a scaling ADC, so Caitlyn's range holds at full build."]}
